condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Section 3.02. (b) | Description :Recipient shall update the Procurement Plan in accordance with guidelinesacceptable to the IDA, and furnish such update to the IDAnot later than 12 months after preceding Procurement Plan | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section 3.03.(a) | Description :Prepare and furnish on basis of guidelines to the IDA, not later than 6 monthsafter the Closing Date or such later date a plan for future operation of the project | Due Date :30-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement :Section 3.04 | Description :Recipient shall within 2 months of the Date of Effectiveness cause PCU to select afirm, satisfactory to IDA, in charge of performing an audit function for the project | Due Date :01-Feb-2006

Finance Agreement :Section 3.05 | Description :Recipient shall, within 12 months of Grant effectiveness, cause PCU to select a firmsatisfactory to IDA for the procurement audit refered in para. 4 of Schedule 4 | Due Date :01-Dec-2006

Finance Agreement :Section 3.06 | Description :Recipient shall, within 3 months of effectiveness, cause PCU to select an EEAsatisfactory to IDA in charge of performing M&E for the project | Due Date :15-Sep-2006

Finance Agreement :Section 3.07 | Description :Recipient shall within 30 days of effectiveness, cause PCU to enter into agreementw/ BCECO satisfactory to IDA to carry Proct, Accting, FM and disbursement activities under the project & adopt PIM | Due Date:31-Dec-2005

Finance Agreement :Section 4.01 (b) (ii) | Description :Recipient shall furnish to IDA, as soon as available not later than 6months after end of each FY (A)Certified copies of financial statements & (B) an opinion on such statements by auditors | Frequency:Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section 4.02 (b) | Description :Furnish to IDA the 1st FMR & subsequent FMRs no later than 45 days after eachsubsequent calendar quarter | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :Section V.1 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the PIM and the PAPAM including the Anti-CorruptionPlan shall be updated. | Due Date :25-Nov-2011

Finance Agreement :Section V.1 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the terms of reference and contract of the currentinternal auditor, shall be updated in a manner satisfactory to the Association to reflect the additional Financing and activitiesto be provided under this Agreement | Due Date :28-Feb-2013

Finance Agreement :Section V.2 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the terms of reference and contract of the currentinternal auditor shall be updated and extended to reflect the Project. | Due Date :25-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Section V.2 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the terms of reference of the external auditors,shall be updated in a manner satisfactory to the Association to reflect the additional Financing and activities to be providedunder this Agreement | Due Date :28-Feb-2013

Finance Agreement :Section V.3 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure an accountant for the PCU shall be engaged under terms ofreference and with experience and qualifications satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :28-Feb-2013
Finance Agreement :Section V.3 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the terms of reference of the external auditors,shall be updated to reflect the Project. | Due Date :25-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Section V.4 | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that the terms of reference contracts with theImplementing Support Partners shall be updated in a manner satisfactory to the Association | Due Date :28-Feb-2013
Finance Agreement :Section VI | Description :IPFF to be adopted by the Recipient | Due Date :30-Jun-2011
